rnatives. Furthermore, we leverage potential-based heuristics (à la Paper 2) at the operator level, now augmented with neural estimates of both cost-to-prove and diversity-potential, enabling scalable guidance in BDD-like representations of proof states. The resulting framework goes beyond accuracy—it fosters *cognitive richness* in automated reasoning, mimicking how human mathematicians explore multiple routes to deepen understanding.

